 Associated Terms for Omnichannel Journeys Using Data Cloud

Activation: The process that publishes a segment to activation platforms (targets).
 Activation Target: The location, including authentication and authorization information, where a segmentâ€™s data is being sent to during activation.
 Attributes: Information or data found in objects. Direct attributes (1:1): Attributes with a direct relationship in a data model object. Related attributes (1:N): Attributes that have a one-to-many relationship.
 Individual: An Individual profile represents an instance of a person from an external system. 
 Unified Individual: A grouping of separate Individual profiles that relate to a single Unified Individual profile.

Marketing Cloud Engagement Terms

Attribute: Information or data about a contact found in a data extension created as part of a Data Cloud activation.
 Attribute Group: A logical grouping of data extensions that make up the Contact Model within Engagement.
 Channel Address: The address where a message is delivered. 
 Contact: A contact represents an instance of a person that you can send messages to.
 Contact Model: A collection of attribute groups that define a person within Engagement.
 Data Extension: A table that stores data in Engagement.
 Data Foundation: An implementation where you activate data from Data Cloud into the Engagement Contact Model.
 Journey: A marketing workflow that orchestrates a series of personalized messages, decision splits, and other activities.
 Omni-Channel Contact: A person represented by one SubscriberKey in Engagement. 
 Single-Channel Contact: A person represented by three different SubscriberKeys in Engagement.
 SubscriberKey: An identifier that represents an instance of a person or contact that you can send messages to.
